##############################################################################
Very Short Term

 - Mat3xN, VecN: operations on SubMat and SubVec 
  (add Mat3xN transposed, add VecN)
 - Mat6xN for piezo beams (2 Mat3xN, with operations)
 - (01-24/26-99) Adaptive GPC and DBC
 - Modify swashplate by eliminating stiffness terms for the inputs (to be
   substituted by corresponding basic genels)
 - add logical and relational DriveCaller (at present fixed with string drive
   caller and new logical and relational math parser)
 - feedforward for GPC and DPC


##############################################################################
Short Term

 - Piezoelectric beams (sensors)
 - (01-27-99) Hydraulic nodes and elements (Puggelli)
 - (done, fix bugs!...) Analytical model for helicopter rotor trim (Peters')
 - Piezo matrices as Constitutive laws <Vec6, Mat6xN> for non-linear piezo
 - BeamLumpedInertia: element that generates lumped inertia for the three nodes
   of a beam element from a 6x6 section constitutive law (or from m, S, J)
 - Automatic generation of nodes, beam elements and beam inertia given a
   macro-beam. 
 - Beam data (and general distributed data) from a data handler that knows 
   how to interpolate from tables and so.
 - Add v2.0 input for structured stuff
 - remove "control data" node/element counters (saving backwards 
   compatibility) and put all the data in STL-like containers.
   First step towards submodel automated generation.



##############################################################################
Mid Term

 - Integration with NUVOLA/Bagai's code for incompressible rotor wake
 - (Cassan ?) Integration with ADAMS Pre/Post Processing
 - Modal deformations (with aerodynamics and inertia, for wing and blades)
 - Parallel (Quaranta) and iterative (?) solution



##############################################################################
Long Term (No Schedule)

 - Translation structural nodes (no rotations, for wires and so)
 - Wire element

